OL,3,CFirst horse dies at Grand National
OL,4,CFestival moments after winning race
OL,6,FThe on-course veterinary team were
OL,7,Fquick to come to his aid, but the
OL,8,FWillie Mullins-trained seven-year-old,
OL,9,Fwho was wearing the colours of
OL,10,FGigginstown House Stud, could not be
OL,11,Fsaved.
OL,13,F"Unfortunately he broke his back and
OL,14,Fthey put him down," said Gigginstown's
OL,15,FEddie O'Leary.
OL,17,F"Paul said he made one mistake and he
OL,18,Ffelt nothing and he kept going to the
OL,19,Fline no problem. It was just when he
OL,20,Fpulled up, unfortunately.
OL,26,@uD@AOUvD@SO]yD@AOU
